Memory cards (e.g., SD, micro-SD) are thin cards designed to fit dedicated slots in cameras, phones, etc., while flash drives (USB sticks) are packaged with a USB connector to plug directly into a USB port. Because of these distinctions, they are not considered the same device, even though they share the underlying flash storage technology.
Marvel’s Daredevil was renewed by Netflix for a third season in 2016, and that season ultimately premiered on October 19, 2018. Therefore, a season 3 does (or did) indeed exist.

In the Season 2 two-part episode of Grey’s Anatomy (‘It’s the End of the World’ / ‘As We Know It’), Meredith removes the explosive device from the patient’s chest. Bomb-squad leader Dylan Young carries it down the hallway, where it detonates, killing him but sparing the hospital staff in the OR. Therefore, the bomb does indeed explode, just not inside the operating room.

The idea that pool water contains a special chemical that turns a vivid color when someone urinates is an urban legend. While urine can react with chlorine to form chloramines (which may contribute to odor and eye irritation), no commonly used pool additive reliably produces an obvious color change. Practically, pools do not change color when someone pees in them.

Davao City, Philippines covers about 2,400 km² and has a population of roughly 1.8 million. Many other cities—whether measured by land area (e.g., Chongqing, China at >80,000 km²) or by population (e.g., Tokyo, Delhi)—are far larger. Therefore, Davao City is not the biggest city in the world by any common metric.

Under normal circumstances an MLB game is played until one team wins, using as many extra innings as needed. However, if play is halted (weather, darkness, curfew, unforeseen events) after the game is official and the score is tied, the contest is recorded as a suspended game to be finished later. If it cannot be resumed before the end of the season and the result has no bearing on postseason qualification, the Commissioner can declare it a tie. This has happened a handful of times in MLB history, so a tie is possible, though extremely rare.

In the English Football League (EFL) play-offs – including those for League Two – the away-goals rule is not applied. If the aggregate score is level after the two legs, the tie goes to extra time and, if necessary, a penalty shoot-out. Therefore, away goals do not provide any tiebreak advantage.

In human genetics, nondisjunction during meiosis can result in an individual receiving two Y chromosomes along with one X chromosome (47,XYY karyotype), a condition known as XYY syndrome. Therefore, the presence of an extra Y chromosome is biologically possible and documented.
The Bahamas is a sovereign nation that gained independence from the United Kingdom in 1973. While geographically close to Florida, it is not a territory, state, or possession of the United States.

The United States Postal Service (USPS) is legally defined as an independent establishment of the executive branch of the U.S. federal government. Although it operates with some businesslike autonomy and does not receive regular tax appropriations for operating expenses, it remains a government agency rather than a privately owned entity.

Poison ivy causes an allergic contact dermatitis characterized by inflammation, redness, and itching. Standard therapy includes topical corticosteroids of medium to high potency for mild-to-moderate cases, with systemic steroids reserved for more severe or widespread reactions. Triamcinolone acetonide cream is a medium-to-high potency topical corticosteroid and is commonly prescribed to decrease the inflammation and pruritus of poison ivy dermatitis, provided it is used as directed and not applied to sensitive areas such as the face or genitals.

answer: Yes, the natural rind is edible (trim off any wax or plastic coating first).
Reasoning: Traditional Port Salut is a washed-rind cheese; the orange rind is formed on the cheese itself and is technically edible, though its flavor is stronger than the interior. Some modern, factory-made Port Salut wheels may have a thin layer of colored wax or plastic over the rind, in which case that outer coating should be trimmed off, but the natural rind beneath is still edible. In general, you can eat the rind of Port Salut, but many people remove it for taste or if a wax coating is present.
Answer: Yes, the natural rind is edible (trim off any wax or plastic coating first).

Reasoning: The standard deviation (SD) measures the variability of individual observations in a population or sample. The standard error (SE), most often the standard error of the mean, measures the variability of a sample statistic (e.g., the sample mean) across repeated samples and equals the population SD divided by the square root of sample size (SD/√n). Thus, while related, they are distinct quantities serving different purposes.

In most cooking terminology—especially in the United States—“cornstarch” refers to the pure starch extracted from the endosperm of the corn kernel, used mainly as a thickening agent. “Corn flour,” on the other hand, usually means finely ground whole-kernel corn (essentially a very fine cornmeal) and still contains protein and fiber. Because they behave differently in recipes, they are generally not considered the same product. (In a few regions such as the U.K., the term “cornflour” is used for cornstarch, but globally the two terms are not interchangeable.)

In formal geometry a rhombus is a quadrilateral whose four sides are all the same length. The informal term “diamond” (or “diamond-shape”) is usually used to describe that exact figure when it is simply rotated so that one vertex points up. Since rotation does not change the underlying properties of the shape, a ‘diamond’ is just a rhombus seen at a different orientation. Because “diamond” is not a strict mathematical term there can be occasional colloquial variations, but in standard mathematical usage the two refer to the same shape.

In production and cost analysis, total cost is comprised of two components: fixed cost (costs that do not vary with output, e.g., rent) and variable cost (costs that change with output, e.g., materials and labor). Therefore, fixed cost is only a part of total cost, not the whole of it, except in the special case where variable cost is zero, which is uncommon.
The TV series 'Witches of East End' aired for only two seasons (2013–2014) on Lifetime before being cancelled. No third season was produced or released.

Thailand spans less than 10 degrees of longitude and officially uses a single national time standard—Indochina Time (ICT, UTC+7)—across the entire country. There are no regional or daylight-saving offsets within Thailand.

Under the Laws of Cricket (formerly Law 41.16, now Law 38.3 after the 2022 code update), a bowler is permitted to run out the non-striker if that batter leaves the crease before the bowler has released the ball. This dismissal, often colloquially called a “Mankad,” is treated exactly like any other run-out and is legal provided it is executed before the completion of the delivery stride.

The Conn Smythe Trophy is usually awarded to a player on the Stanley Cup-winning team, but there have been several exceptions. It has been given to a player on the losing team five times: Roger Crozier (1966), Glenn Hall (1968), Reggie Leach (1976), Ron Hextall (1987) and Jean-Sébastien Giguère (2003). Therefore, the trophy has indeed gone to a player whose team lost in the Final.

Under modern contract law, although the doctrine of privity generally limits enforcement rights to the contracting parties themselves, an intended third-party beneficiary (as opposed to a mere incidental beneficiary) acquires the right to enforce the promise once the contract is formed and the beneficiary’s rights have vested. Therefore, such a beneficiary may bring an action for breach of contract against the promisor.

The Kingdom of Romania itself was never incorporated into Austria-Hungary; it was an independent state during the empire’s existence (1867-1918). However, several regions that are now part of modern Romania—most notably Transylvania, Bukovina and parts of Banat, Crișana and Maramureș—were inside the Austro-Hungarian borders. Thus, while territories with Romanian populations were in the empire, the country of Romania was not.

Ruby and sapphire are both varieties of the mineral corundum (Al₂O₃ with different trace elements). Garnet, however, is a completely different group of silicate minerals with distinct chemical compositions. Simply combining or mixing ruby and sapphire would not change their crystal structure or chemistry to become garnet.

The U.S. Navy retired the F-14 in 2006, but the Iranian Air Force, which acquired the type before the 1979 revolution, continues to keep a limited number airworthy and in operational use. Because they remain in active service with Iran, the statement that F-14 Tomcats are still in service is correct.

In the original 2006 series finale of Will & Grace, Grace Adler is shown giving birth to a daughter, Laila, fathered by her husband Leo. Although the 2017 revival later retconned that finale as a dream and reset Grace to being childless, within the original run she indeed had a baby on-screen.

Mainland Spain (including the Balearic Islands, Ceuta and Melilla) observes Central European Time (UTC+1, UTC+2 in summer). The Canary Islands, which are also part of Spain, observe Western European Time (UTC+0, UTC+1 in summer). Therefore, Spain spans two different time zones.

In English collective noun usage, the accepted term for a group of domestic cats is ‘a clowder’ (another, less common term is ‘a glaring’). Therefore, stating that a group of cats is known as a clowder is correct.

Fixed costs are costs that do not change with the level of production (e.g., rent, salaried administrative staff). Overhead costs are indirect costs needed to run the business that cannot be traced directly to a product or service (e.g., rent, utilities, indirect labor). While many overhead items are fixed, some overhead can be variable (such as utility bills that rise with machine hours). Therefore, although there is overlap—many fixed costs are overhead—‘fixed’ and ‘overhead’ describe different attributes, and the two terms are not synonymous.

Arrested Development originally aired three seasons on Fox (2003-2006). Netflix later revived the show, releasing season 4 in 2013 and subsequently producing and releasing season 5 in two parts (2018 and 2019). Therefore, a fifth season exists.

The U.S. has 63 congressionally designated national parks, and they are located in only about 30 states and U.S. territories. Several states—including Delaware, Connecticut, Rhode Island, and others—do not contain a national park. Therefore, not every state has one.

The standard ITV Hub service, which includes on-demand shows and live channels with advertising, is available free of charge. A paid tier (ITV Hub+) exists that removes adverts and adds downloads, but payment is not required to use the basic service. Therefore the statement that you have to pay to use ITV Hub is incorrect.

A characteristic (intensive) property does not depend on the amount of the substance and can be used to help identify or distinguish one substance from another. The boiling point is intrinsic to the substance (at a given pressure) and is commonly used to characterize and identify materials, so it qualifies as a characteristic property of matter.

Kermit the Frog, created by Jim Henson, is best known as the central character of The Muppet Show, but he also appeared regularly on Sesame Street in its early years, most notably as a news reporter in the "Sesame Street News Flash" sketches. His appearances are well-documented in Sesame Street episodes and official materials.

The lyrics of the UK national anthem are adapted to reflect the gender of the reigning monarch. When the monarch is male, the anthem is sung as “God Save the King”; when the monarch is female, it is sung as “God Save the Queen.” Therefore, the anthem does change (in wording, not melody) if there is a king instead of a queen.

In skeletal muscle, the muscle fiber (also called a muscle cell) is a large, multinucleated cell that contains many myofibrils. A myofibril is a cylindrical bundle of contractile proteins (actin and myosin) inside the muscle fiber. Therefore, a myofibril is a structural component within a muscle fiber, not another name for the whole muscle fiber itself.

Many intersections are still equipped with simple signal heads that have no imaging devices. While some traffic lights do have red-light enforcement cameras or traffic-flow monitoring cameras mounted nearby, this technology is deployed only at selected locations where officials decide it is needed and can justify the cost. Therefore, it is not true that every traffic light has a camera.
Jaguar and Land Rover are brands that were acquired from Ford by India’s Tata Motors in 2008 and have since been operated as the combined company Jaguar Land Rover under Tata’s ownership.

New York Life Insurance Company is organized as a mutual insurance company, meaning it is owned by its policyholders rather than shareholders and its stock is not traded on public exchanges. Therefore, it is not considered a public company.

Time Warner Cable began as a division of the media conglomerate Time Warner, but it was fully spun off as a separate, independent company in 2009. After the spin-off it operated on its own and was later acquired by Charter Communications in 2016, whereas Time Warner (now WarnerMedia) remained a different corporation. Therefore, they are not the same company.

Historically and at present, the Canadian dollar (CAD) has most often traded below the U.S. dollar (USD); recent exchange rates place 1 CAD at roughly 0.73–0.78 USD. Therefore the Canadian dollar is generally worth less than the U.S. dollar.

The Disney theme-park attraction “Pirates of the Caribbean,” which opened at Disneyland in 1967, served as the direct inspiration for the 2003 film “Pirates of the Caribbean: The Curse of the Black Pearl” and the subsequent movie franchise. Therefore, the films were indeed based on the ride.

The original iPhone 6 was released in September 2014. The first iPhone SE model did not arrive until March 2016 (and later SE versions came out even further after). Therefore, the iPhone SE was introduced after—not before—the iPhone 6.

New England is composed of Maine, New Hampshire, Vermont, Massachusetts, Rhode Island, and Connecticut. Each of these states had legally abolished slavery well before 1854: Vermont (1777), Massachusetts (1783), Rhode Island (gradual emancipation culminating 1843), Connecticut (gradual emancipation culminating 1848), New Hampshire (gradual emancipation, no slaves recorded by 1850), and Maine (free when admitted in 1820). Therefore, in 1854 every New England state was a free state.

The Titius–Bode ‘law’ is an empirical spacing rule that was devised to fit the Solar System; it has no solid physical derivation. When astronomers test the many multi-planet exoplanetary systems now known, some can be forced to fit a Titius–Bode–type sequence, but just as many (or more) do not, and statistical studies show no systematic adherence. The architectures of exoplanet systems are far more diverse than the simple geometric progression required by the rule. Therefore, as a general statement, exoplanetary systems do not follow the Titius–Bode rule.

Historically, the condition now called bipolar disorder was referred to as manic-depressive illness or manic depression. Modern diagnostic manuals (e.g., DSM-5, ICD-11) use the term bipolar disorder, but it describes the same underlying illness characterized by episodes of mania/hypomania and depression.

Compton Mackenzie’s novel “Whisky Galore,” and the subsequent film adaptations, were inspired by the real 1941 wreck of the SS Politician off the island of Eriskay in the Outer Hebrides. The cargo included thousands of cases of whisky that local islanders famously salvaged, an episode that forms the core of the story in the book and movie. Thus the plot is rooted in an actual historical event, though details were fictionalized.

The ISS routinely hosts plant-growth experiments (e.g., Veggie, Advanced Plant Habitat) where astronauts cultivate lettuces, zinnias, dwarf wheat, etc. Although individual plant batches are harvested and replaced, at any given time there are usually living plants aboard for research, so plants are indeed present on the station.

Under standard ice-hockey rules (e.g., NHL, IIHF), a goal is awarded only when the entire puck completely crosses the goal line, between the posts and beneath the cross-bar. If any part of the puck remains on or above the line, play continues and no goal is counted. Therefore, for a goal to be valid, the puck must fully cross the line.

The TV series 'Shadowhunters' was officially cancelled by its network, Freeform, after its third season in 2018. A two-episode finale (“The Final Hunt”) was produced to conclude the story, and since then no credible announcements from the network, producers, or cast have indicated a revival or continuation. Industry coverage continues to describe the series as definitively ended, so a fifth season is not planned.
